{
  "description": "PNW College Baseball Park Factors \u2014 empirical-Bayes blend of measured park conditions and six-season home/road run splits.",
  "methodology": "Park Index centered at 100 (>100 favors hitters). Each park blends a physical prior (elevation with altitude saturation, outfield depth vs 350 ft, temperature) with its observed home/road run split, weighted by sample size (games/(games+300)). Coefficients from leave-one-season-out cross-validation, 2021-2026. Indices re-centered (games-weighted) so the average PNW park = 100. Built on the Park Factors tool by Kai Malloch (intern, June 2026).",
